
12. October Revolution
Briefing
Having accepted the bid for power from Gladkov's group, Burlak must now rid the world of comrade general Platonov, for ever.

Co-ordinates
V. K. Bluekher base, October 25, 2 NR

Dialogue
Designer's notes
The player starts in vicinity of Bluekher base. His task is to defeat the forces of general Platonov. To do so, he must capture three of the five bases in this area. While each base can be captured by brute force, there is also an alternative in each case:

Kill commander
Intimidate commander (by gathering large force in the vicinity of his base)
Persuade commander (Answer quiz)
Pay commander (with something from different base)
Beat commander

The player will learn about these possibilities through queries and dialogues. When he captures the first base, it will be his completely (all men, all buildings) in all next cases, the commander gives him only some men, and keeps the base.  The number of men player receives is in parentheses. The player starts with 3 men.

A - 14
B - 13 (5) - to intimidate player needs at least 12 men
C - 5 (3) - never gets the commander
D - 8 (2) - never gets the commander + 3 scientists + space-time lab
E - 9 (5)

His secondary objective is stop Gossudarov from joining the Alliance and keep the Artefact (this is primary obj. as it is necessary for next mission).

The map is roughly square and very big, with a base in upper left, lower left and lower right corner, and in the centre of top and right edge.

Character selection
There is no character selection, all the player gets are Gladkov and his cadets.

Dialogue Start (Burlak and Gladkov standing in the open, with couple of other characters nearby)
{
Burlak: = So where is everyone?
Gladkov: = They are all here.
Burlak: = This is it!? You said there were many who supported you.
Gladkov: = They do, but they are too afraid to show themselves.
Burlak: = (sarcastic) Brilliant!
Gladkov: = But knowing our supporters are there, means once we have demonstrated our strength the battle will be won quickly. I believe four bases under our command would be enough for victory.
Burlak: = Do you have a list of the targets comrade Gladkov?
Gladkov: = There is A. I. Yegorov base in South West, commanded by colonel Tsarytsyn. He is a hard-line communist but if we can persuade him our cause is for the people he may join us.
Gladkov: = To the South East there is M. N. Ryutin base, under command of colonel Davidov. He's a little mad, spends too much time in the lab with scientists.
Gladkov: = In East there is Y. E. Yakir base, commanded by colonel Eisenstein. He's a bully but can be bullied as well!
Gladkov: = There is M. A. Budonny base in the North, it's commanded by colonel Borodin. He is weak man out for himself, he will go with the one who has the upper hand.
Gladkov: = There is V. K. Bluekher base in North West (camera pans). Obviously this is commanded by Platonov, so we can only use force here.
Gladkov: = Of course, if we just went straight for Platonov and defeated him the rest would follow then. This could prevent many casualties. But the decision is yours comrade. We follow your command.
}

